{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17504666","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17504666"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:18:28+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:18:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2353"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2353","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2353"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.77,0.05,0.04,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2353"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"45730"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2353","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2353"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2353"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"30658"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"41"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"735"},{"type":"tags","id":"1243"},{"type":"tags","id":"1244"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"5826"},{"type":"tags","id":"6094"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1369"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1374"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42473"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43132"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"45730","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/45730"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 30 year old man presents to the Emergency Department following an injury from a tackle during a game of football. During the game, he was tackled on his right shoulder as he was reaching out for the ball. Immediately after the tackle, he was found lying on the floor clutching his right shoulder in pain.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears in pain and the right shoulder is abducted and externally rotated. His right elbow remains flexed and forearm internally rotated, supported by the other hand. There is no loss of skin integrity on his right shoulder, but the acromion appears prominent as compared to the left shoulder. His vital signs are stable, and he has a normal radial pulse on both arms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn X-ray of the shoulder is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely area of sensory loss in his right upper limb as a result of this injury?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Medial aspect of his right upper arm","Lateral aspect of his right upper arm","Medial aspect of his right forearm","Lateral aspect of his right forearm","Dorsal aspect of his right hand"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with shoulder pain and a shoulder that is abducted and externally rotated with a prominent acromion. This is consistent with an anterior dislocation of the shoulder, commonly due to an anteriorly directed force on the arm as the shoulder is abducted and externally rotated.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDamage to the axillary nerve is a complication that may result from a shoulder dislocation as the nerve courses medially to the surgical neck of the humerus. This may affect the sensory innervation of the \u003Cstrong\u003Elateral aspect of the upper arm\u003C/strong\u003E, as the posterior terminal branch of the axillary nerve innervates the upper lateral cutaneous nerve of the arm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe sensory innervation of the medial aspect of the upper arm comes from the intercostobrachial and medial cutaneous nerve. The sensory innervation of the lateral aspect of the forearm comes from the musculocutaneous nerve, and the medial aspect of the forearm is from the medial antebrachial cutaneous nerve. The radial nerve predominantly innervates the dorsal aspect of the hand. The ulnar nerve also innervates the dorsal aspect of the little finger and \u00bd of the ring finger. The aforementioned nerves could be injured by arm or forearm fractures.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Potential axillary nerve injury must always be considered in dislocation of the shoulder"],"references":["Visser CP, Coene LN, Brand R, Tavy DL. The incidence of nerve injury in anterior dislocation of the shoulder and its influence on functional recovery. A prospective clinical and EMG study. J Bone Joint Surg Br 1999; 81:679.","Cleeman E, Flatow EL. Shoulder dislocations in the young patient. Orthop Clin North Am 2000; 31:217.","Gaillard, F., 2021. Anterior shoulder dislocation | Radiology Case | Radiopaedia.org. [online] Radiopaedia.org. Available at: \u003Chttps://radiopaedia.org/cases/anterior-shoulder-dislocation-1?lang=gb\u003E."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"30658"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2353"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"18405"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"18405","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/18405"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/7d9ba1bc-1e24-45a7-bda4-6ac27f43f6f0.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/7d9ba1bc-1e24-45a7-bda4-6ac27f43f6f0.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":559,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"30658","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/30658"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-05-20T19:25:33+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-05-20T